{
  "texts": [
    "This simplifies the problem of deconvolution considerably but can lead to some problems, e.g.",
    "the caustic can be discontinuous in the case of a cusp, it can have significant curvature, and magnification can vary along its direction (Agol and Krolik 1999).",
    "It turns out that the latter two can be resolved if the source has a size of 10% of θ E (Grieger et al. 1988).",
    "This method has been demonstrated to be stable on simulations using basic regularization schemes (see Benning and Burger 2018, for a review), showing potential of resolving the accretion disc structure within a few gravitational radii from the central SMBH.",
    "When it comes to real observations, the best and only system to provide the necessary HMEs has been the quadruply lensed quasar Q 2237+0305."
  ]
}